The hexapod walker consisted of 3 key physical components

  1. Base
  2. Upper Leg
  3. Lower Leg

The base was the backbone of the hexapod walker, where the majority of electrical components were conected to and the PCB connected to.

Each leg for the hexapod walker considted of a upper leg and lower leg:
  - the upper leg was in charge of the leg's horizontal motion
  - the lower leg was in charge of the leg's vertical motion
